  42                     _ begs.push(i)

  53             if begs.length
  54                 set result = [left, right]

 232                     @ parents ret
 233     var normalizePath
 234         function
 235             param path
 236             return verify.replaceAll(path, '\\', '/')
 237     var merge
 238         function
 239             param obj1
 240             param obj2
 241             var
 242                 decl mobj
 243                     {
 244                 decl attrname
 245             for attrname in obj1
 246                 set mobj[attrname] = obj1[attrname]
 247             for attrname in obj2
 248                 set mobj[attrname] = obj2[attrname]
 249             return mobj

src/ittf/_old/lib/repo/sanitize.js.ittf



   1 module wizzi-repo.sanitize
   2     kind jsfile
   3     #
   4     # NOT USED YET
   5     #
   6     # / ? < > \ : * | "
   7     var illegalRe = /[\/\?<>\\:\*\|":]/g
   8     +
   9     # Unicode Control codes
  10     # C0 0x00-0x1f & C1 (0x80-0x9f)
  11     # http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C0_and_C1_control_codes
  12     var controlRe = /[\x00-\x1f\x80-\x9f]/g
  13     +
  14     # Reserved filenames on Unix-based systems (".", "..")
  15     var reservedRe = /^\.+$/
  16     +
  17     # Reserved filenames in Windows ("CON", "PRN", "AUX", "NUL", "COM1",
  18     # "COM2", "COM3", "COM4", "COM5", "COM6", "COM7", "COM8", "COM9",
  19     # "LPT1", "LPT2", "LPT3", "LPT4", "LPT5", "LPT6", "LPT7", "LPT8", and
  20     # "LPT9") case-insesitively and with or without filename extensions.
  21     var windowsReservedRe = /^(con|prn|aux|nul|com[0-9]|lpt[0-9])(\..*)?$/i
  22     +
  23     function sanitize
  24         string input
  25         string replacement
  26             optional
  27         return
  28             _ input.replace(illegalRe, replacement)
  29                 ._ replace(controlRe, replacement)
  30                     ._ replace(reservedRe, replacement)
  31                         ._ replace(windowsReservedRe, replacement)
  32     +
  33     set module.exports =
  34         function
  35             string input
  36             { options
  37                 optional
  38             var
  39                 decl replacement = options && options.replacement || ''
  40                 decl output = sanitize(input, replacement)
  41             if replacement === ''
  42                 return output
  43             return sanitize(output, '')

   1 module ${name}
   2     $params name
   3     kind jsfile
   4     +
   5     #
   6         # EXAMPLE: ${name}
   7     +
   8     var myname = '${name}'
   9     +
  10     import util
  11     import path
  12     var stringify = require('json-stringify-safe')
  13     var vfile = require('wizzi-utils').vfile
  14     # defaults to filesystem
  15     var fsfile = vfile()
  16     var verify = require('wizzi-utils').verify
  17     $hook imports
  18     +
  19     $hook
  20     function heading1
  21         param text
  22         log ''
  23         log '********************************************************************************'
  24         log '** Example ${name} - ' + text
  25         log '********************************************************************************'
  26         log ''
  27     function heading2
  28         param text
  29         log ''
  30         log '--------------------------------------------------------------------------------'
  31         log '-- Example ${name} - ' + text
  32         log '--------------------------------------------------------------------------------'
  33         log ''
  34     function printArray
  35         param name
  36         param arr
  37         param fields
  38         log '* array ' + name + ' : '
  39         foreach item in arr
  40             log '  {', i
  41             var keys = fields || Object.keys(item)
  42             foreach k in keys
  43                 _ printValue
  44                     @ k
  45                     @ item[k]
  46     function printValue
  47         param k
  48         param v
  49         if verify.isNotEmpty(v)
  50             var lines
  51                 _ verify.splitLines
  52                     @ v
  53                     {
  54                         @ numbered true
  55             if lines.length === 1
  56                 log '   ', k, ':', lines[0].text
  57             else
  58                 for var i=0; i<lines.length; i++
  59                     if i === 0
  60                         log '   ', k, ':', lines[0].numFmt, lines[0].text
  61                     else
  62                         log '   ', spaces(k.length+1), ' ', lines[i].numFmt, lines[i].text
  63         else
  64             log '   ', k, ':', v
  65     function spaces
  66         param len
  67         return new Array(len).join(' ')

src/ittf/lib/json/directoryTree.js.ittf



   1 module
   2     kind es6
   3     # forked from https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mihneadb/node-directory-tree/master/lib/directory-tree.js
   4     const FS = require('fs')
   5     const PATH = require('path')
   6     const constants
   7         {
   8             @ DIRECTORY 1
   9             @ FILE 2
  10     function safeReadDirSync
  11         param path
  12         let dirData = {}
  13         try
  14             set dirData = FS.readdirSync(path)
  15         catch ex
  16             if ex.code == "EACCES"
  17                 # User does not have permissions, ignore directory
  18                 return null
  19             else
  20                 throw ex
  21         return dirData
  22     function normalizePath
  23         param path
  24         return path.replace(/\\/g, '/')
  25     function isRegExp
  26         param regExp
  27         return typeof regExp === "object" && regExp.constructor == RegExp
  28     function directoryTree
  29         param path
  30         const name = PATH.basename(path);
  31         set path = normalizePath(path)
  32         const item
  33             {
  34                 @ path
  35                 @ name
  36         let stats
  37         try
  38             set stats = FS.statSync(path)
  39         catch e
  40             return null
  41         # log 'stats', stats
  42         if stats.isFile()
  43             const ext = PATH.extname(path).toLowerCase();
  44             # Skip if it does not match the extension regex
  45             log 'ext', ext
  46             if ext != '.ittf'
  47                 return null
  48             # File size in bytes
  49             # set item.size = stats.size
  50             # set item.extension = ext
  51             set item.type = constants.FILE
  52         elif stats.isDirectory()
  53             let dirData = safeReadDirSync(path)
  54             if dirData === null
  55                 return null
  56             set item.children = []
  57             set item.type = constants.DIRECTORY
  58             foreach child in dirData
  59                 _ item.children.push
  60                     _ directoryTree
  61                         _ PATH.join
  62                             @ path
  63                             @ child
  64         else
  65             return null
  66         return item
  67     set module.exports = directoryTree

src/ittf/lib/mongodb/mongoUriParser.js.ittf



   1 module wizzi-repo.mongodb.mongoUriParser
   2     kind jsfile
   3     import path
   4     import url
   5     var verify = require('wizzi-utils').verify
   6     #
   7         # In a mongodb repo, documents are stored
   8         # per user and per project.
   9         # Document uris must be in the form
  10         # db://userName/projectName/documentPath
  11         # The internal db path will be
  12         # `config.mongoDbBaseFolder`/userName/projectName/documentPath
  13         # params
  14         # string uri
  15         # string mongodbBaseFolder
  16         # returns
  17         # {
  18         # string originalUri
  19         # string userId
  20         # string projectId
  21         # string path
  22         # string storeKind
  23         # boolean isIttfDocument
  24         # string basename
  25         # string schema
  26         # string extension
  27     set module.exports
  28         function parse
  29             string uri
  30             string mongodbBaseFolder
  31             set uri = uri.toLowerCase()
  32             var ret
  33                 {
  34                     @ originalUri uri
  35             var parsedUri = url.parse(uri)
  36             if typeof(parsedUri.protocol) !== 'string'
  37                 r_wz_err( InvalidArgument,  parse )
  38                     @ 'Uri must have a protocol (must be an absolute url). Received: ' + uri
  39             var protocol
  40                 iif parsedUri.protocol.substr(-1, 1) === ':'
  41                     then
  42                         _ parsedUri.protocol.substr(0, (parsedUri.protocol.length - 1))
  43                     else
  44                         set parsedUri.protocol
  45             if protocol !== 'db'
  46                 r_wz_err( InvalidArgument,  parse )
  47                     @ 'Invalid uri protocol. Must be `db`. Received: ' + uri
  48             # log 'parseuri.parsedUri', parsedUri
  49             var
  50                 decl name
  51                 decl parts = parsedUri.pathname ? parsedUri.pathname.split('/') : []
  52             if parsedUri.pathname && parsedUri.pathname.length > 0 && parsedUri.pathname[0] == '/'
  53                 _ parts.shift()
  54             set name = parts[parts.length-1]
  55             set ret.basename = name
  56             var nameparts = name.split('.')
  57             if nameparts.length > 2 && nameparts[nameparts.length -1] === 'ittf'
  58                 set ret.isIttfDocument = true
  59                 set ret.schema = nameparts[nameparts.length -2]
  60             else
  61                 set ret.isIttfDocument = false
  62                 set ret.extension = nameparts[nameparts.length -1]
  63             if parts.length < 1
  64                 r_wz_err( InvalidArgument,  parse )
  65                     {
  66                         @ parameter 'uri'
  67                         @ message 'A mongodb uri must be in the form `db://userName/projectName/documentPath`. Received: ' + uri
  68             # log 'wizzi-repo.mongodb.uriparser.parsedUri.parts', parts
  69             # log 'wizzi-repo.mongodb.uriparser.parsedUri', parsedUri
  70             set ret.storeKind = 'mongodb'
  71             set ret.userId = parsedUri.host
  72             set ret.projectId = parts[0]
  73             _ parts.shift();
  74             set ret.path = parts.join('/')
  75             if mongodbBaseFolder && mongodbBaseFolder.length > 0
  76                 set ret.internalPath
  77                     _ verify.unixifyPath
  78                         _ path.join
  79                             @ mongodbBaseFolder
  80                             @ ret.userId
  81                             @ ret.projectId
  82                             @ ret.path
  83             # log 'parseuri.ret', ret
  84             return ret

src/ittf/lib/repo/uriParser.js.ittf



   1 module wizzi-repo.uriParser
   2     kind jsfile
   3     #
   4         # params
   5         # string uri
   6         # returns
   7         # {
   8         # string originalUri
   9         # string protocol
  10         # one-of 'db', 'ls', drive letter
  11         # string storeKind
  12         # one-of 'mongodb', 'localstorage', 'filesystem'
  13         # string userId
  14         # # if storeKind === 'mongodb'
  15         # string projectId
  16         # # if storeKind === 'mongodb'
  17         # string path
  18         # boolean isIttfDocument
  19         # string basename
  20         # string schema
  21         # # if isIttfDocument === true
  22         # string extension
  23         # # if isIttfDocument === false
  24         #
  25     import url
  26     set module.exports
  27         function parse
  28             string uri
  29             callback
  30             set uri = uri.toLowerCase()
  31             var ret
  32                 {
  33                     @ originalUri uri
  34             var parsedUri = url.parse(uri)
  35             if typeof(parsedUri.protocol) !== 'string'
  36                 r_cb_wz_err( InvalidArgument,  parse )
  37                     @ 'Uri must have a protocol (must be an absolute url). Received: ' + uri
  38             var protocol
  39                 iif parsedUri.protocol.substr(-1, 1) === ':'
  40                     then
  41                         _ parsedUri.protocol.substr(0, (parsedUri.protocol.length - 1))
  42                     else
  43                         set parsedUri.protocol
  44             # log 'parseuri.parsedUri', parsedUri
  45             set ret.protocol = protocol
  46             if protocol === 'db'
  47                 set ret.storeKind = 'mongodb'
  48             elif protocol === 'ls'
  49                 set ret.storeKind = 'localstorage'
  50             else
  51                 if protocol.length === 1
  52                     set ret.storeKind = 'filesystem'
  53                 else
  54                     r_cb_wz_err( InvalidArgument,  parse )
  55                         @ 'Uri protocol must be `db` or `ls` or a filesystem drive letter. Received: ' + protocol
  56             +
  57             var name, parts = parsedUri.pathname ? parsedUri.pathname.split('/') : []
  58             if parsedUri.pathname && parsedUri.pathname.length > 0 && parsedUri.pathname[0] == '/'
  59                 _ parts.shift()
  60             set name = parts[parts.length-1]
  61             set ret.basename = name
  62             var nameparts = name.split('.')
  63             if nameparts.length > 2 && nameparts[nameparts.length -1] === 'ittf'
  64                 set ret.isIttfDocument = true
  65                 set ret.schema = nameparts[nameparts.length -2]
  66             else
  67                 set ret.isIttfDocument = false
  68                 set ret.extension = nameparts[nameparts.length -1]
  69             if ret.storeKind === 'mongodb'
  70                 if parts.length < 1
  71                     r_cb_wz_err( InvalidArgument,  parse )
  72                         {
  73                             @ parameter 'uri'
  74                             @ message 'A mongodb uri must be in the form `db://userName/projectName/documentPath`. Received: ' + uri
  75                 # log 'wizzi-repo.fs.uriparser.parsedUri.parts', parts
  76                 # log 'wizzi-repo.fs.uriparser.parsedUri', parsedUri
  77                 set ret.userId = parsedUri.host
  78                 set ret.projectId = parts[0]
  79                 _ parts.shift();
  80                 set ret.path = parts.join('/')
  81             else
  82                 set ret.path = parts.join('/')
  83             # log 'parseuri.ret', ret
  84             return
  85                 _ callback
  86                     @ null
  87                     @ ret

src/ittf/lib/utils/_ild_objectId.js.ittf



   1 module
   2     kind jsfile
   3     const os = require('os')
   4     const crypto = require('crypto')
   5     class ObjectId
   6         ctor
   7             param id
   8             if id
   9                 set this.id = id
  10                 set this.generationTime = new Date()
  11                 return
  12             #
  13                 # Generates a MongoDB-style ObjectId in Node.js. Uses nanosecond timestamp in place of counter;
  14                 # should be impossible for same process to generate multiple objectId in same nanosecond? (clock
  15                 # drift can result in an *extremely* remote possibility of id conflicts).
  16                 # @returns {string} Id in same format as MongoDB ObjectId.
  17             const seconds = Math.floor(new Date()/1000).toString(16)
  18             const machineId = crypto.createHash('md5').update(os.hostname()).digest('hex').slice(0, 6)
  19             const processId = process.pid.toString(16).slice(0, 4).padStart(4, '0')
  20             const counter = process.hrtime()[1].toString(16).slice(0, 6).padStart(6, '0')
  21             set this.id = seconds + machineId + processId + counter
  22             set this.generationTime = new Date()
  23         m equals
  24             param otherID
  25             return this.id == otherID.id
  26         m toString
  27             return this.id
  28     set module.exports = ObjectId

  11     var ObjectID
  12         function ObjectID
  13             param id

src/ittf/tests/t/fscommon/document/readFile.js.ittf



   1 $group
   2     m readFile
   3         param filePath
   4         param callback
   5         set filePath = normalize(filePath)
   6         var that = this
   7         _ this.fsdb.getItemByPath
   8             @ filePath
   9             f_cb( fsitem )
  10                 if fsitem == null
  11                     throw Error('MongoFS error. Document does not exists: ' + path)
  12                 elif fsitem.kind == 0
  13                     throw Error('MongoFS error. Cannot read a folder: ' + path)
  14                 else
  15                     that.fsdb.readDocumentile
  16                         @ fsitem._id
  17                         f_cb( content )
  18                             return
  19                                 _ callback(content)

src/ittf/tests/t/fscommon/document/write_read_File.js.ittf



   1 $group
   2     var folderPathOld = "c:/my/starters/darvin"
   3     var filePathOld = "c:/my/starters/darvin/hello.md"
   4     var filePathNew = "c:/my/newfolder/readme.md"
   5     var content = "Hello world"
   6     describe write a file
   7         before-async
   8             _ doc.createFolder
   9                 @ folderPathOld
  10                 f_cb_done( f )

  13                 @ filePathNew
  14                 @ content
  15                 f_cb_done( r )
  16                     log 'should write a file', err, r
  17                     tobe_string( r.code,  DOCUMENT_WRITTEN )
  18                     tobe_string_value( r.item.content,  content )
  19         $*
  20         it-async should be not modified
  21             _ doc.writeFile
  22                 @ filePathNew
  23                 @ content
  24                 f_cb_done( r )
  25                     log 'should be not modified', err, r
  26                     tobe_string( r.code,  DOCUMENT_NOT_MODIFIED )
  27         it-async should write into an existing folder
  28             _ doc.writeFile
  29                 @ filePathOld
  30                 @ content
  31                 f_cb_done( r )
  32                     log 'should write into an existing folder', err, r
  33                     tobe_string( r.code,  DOCUMENT_WRITTEN )
  34                     tobe_string_value( r.item.content,  content )
  35         it-async should read
  36             _ doc.readFile
  37                 @ filePathOld
  38                 f_cb_done( r )
  39                     log 'should read', err, r
  40                     tobe_string_value( r,  content )
  41         it-async should overwrite an existing file
  42             _ doc.writeFile
  43                 @ filePathOld
  44                 @ content + ' ' + content
  45                 f_cb_done( r )
  46                     log 'should overwrite an existing file', err, r
  47                     tobe_string( r.code,  DOCUMENT_WRITTEN )
  48                     tobe_string_value( r.item.content,  content + ' ' + content )
  49         *$

  18                     tobe_string( content,  'Hello wizzi factory' )

  26                     tobe_false( stat.isDirectory() )

src/generate.wfjob.ittf

   2     $
   3         var ittf_meta_folder     = path.join(__dirname, 'ittf', 'meta');
   4         var ittf_lib_folder      = path.join(__dirname, 'ittf', 'lib');
   5         var ittf_root_folder     = path.join(__dirname, 'ittf', 'root');
   6         var ittf_examples_folder = path.join(__dirname, 'ittf', 'examples');
   7         var ittf_tests_folder    = path.join(__dirname, 'ittf', 'tests');
   8         var dest_folder           = path.join(__dirname, '..', 'dist');
   9     model meta
  10         schema json
  11         src ${ittf_meta_folder}/index.json.ittf
  12     $include wfjob/lib
  13     $include wfjob/examples
  14     $include wfjob/root
  15     $include wfjob/tests
  16     production
  17         dest-folder ${dest_folder}
  18         line-ref ittf-lib
  19         line-ref ittf-root
  20         line-ref ittf-examples
  21         line-ref ittf-tests
